Dev merge into master (#4)

* RK Code Review

- Fixed indentation bug that made the code almost unreadable.
- Update BWA from 0.7.15 to 0.7.17.
   Reason: Bugfixes in BWA.
- Update SAMTOOLS from 1.3.1 to 1.6.
   Reason: Bugfixes in SAMTOOLS. The program samtools rmdup is
   obsolete. Please switch in a further update to fixmate and markdup.
   The mpileup file contains now always every column. Therefore, our
   workaround in the parse_mpile subroutine in TBtools is obsolete.
   Please update the code according to it. Samtools has now the option
   to print every genome position, also uncovered positions. Therefore,
   iteration along the genome after parallel processing of the mpileup
   file in parse_mpile in TBtools is obsolete. Please update the code
   according to it.
- Update GATK from 3.6 to 3.8.
   Important notification: GATK is becoming open source. Next year
   GATK 4.0 will be released. Please read the release note to GATK
   because the programs IndelRealigner
   IndelTargetCreator etc. are obsolete.
- Update IGVtools from 2.3.88 to 2.3.98.
   Reason: Bugfixes in IGVtools.
- Update Picard-Tools from 2.7.1 to 2.17.0.
   Reason: Modification in dictionary creation and Bugfixes in Picard-
   Tools.

- Removed TBmerge from "lib"

Reason: After removing obsolete third party software IGVTools, some minor code adjustments in this scripts were necessary. The updates come with a speed increase for each sample iteration. (20 seconds per sample when using 2 cores).
*Removed the index files created by BWA, Picard and Samtools from the repository.
Reason: An initial run after installing MTBseq should create system specific index files.

* Added ".idx" file for GATK bascall recalibration routine

*Executing MTBseq on mounted hardisks can result with with an error in the GATK bascalling recalibration routine. The index file ".idx" that is created and used during basecalling recalibraion may be not writeable on such systems. The added ".idx" file should solve the problem
